POSITION

Analyst, Investor Relations

REPORTS TO:

Vice President, Investor Relations

DEPARTMENT:

AlphaCat Capital

PERSONS TO BE SUPERVISED

None

FLSA STATUS

EXEMPTED

POSITION SUMMARY:

The Analyst, Investor Relations will assist in the full range of investor marketing activities including preparing investor materials, assisting in investor communications and meetings, and maintaining marketing intelligence and investor database repository.

KEY RESPONSIBILITES, INCLUDE BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO:


Drafting, editing and production of investor marketing materials including materials required for regular investor calls/meetings and fund marketing materials;
Coordinate and assist in the completion of required investor due diligence materials;
Work within the Investor Relations team to prepare for and participate in meetings with existing and potential investors including ongoing relationship meetings, solicitations and due diligence sessions;
Maintain investor communication records through our investor CRM database repository;
Monitoring trade publications & news sources to identify potential investors and new business opportunities;
Other duties as required.
REQUIRED SKILLS /EXPERIENCE/QUALIFICATIONS:


Minimum 2 years' experience in a professional services role such as investment banking, asset management, investment consulting or similar;
Bachelor's degree in Economics or related subject from accredited university;
Substantial knowledge of global capital markets including potential investors, common products and rules and regulations;
Knowledge of collateralized reinsurance and ILS market preferred;
The ability to deal effectively and courteously with clients and colleagues, and to exercise discretion and confidentiality in all matters;
Excellent written, presentation creation and verbal communication skills; a thorough command of the English language including excellent spelling, grammar and punctuation;
Must be willing to travel and work outside of normal office hours including evenings, weekends and public holidays if necessary;
Proficiency with the Microsoft Office suite of applications;
Proven organizational, self-management and timekeeping skills.
QUALIFICATIONS FOR CONTINUED EMPLOYMENT


Adherence to all Human Resource Policies and Practices
Execution of key duties and responsibilities at a high level
Punctuality and regular attendance
About AIG


