Prudential has a longstanding commitment to allocating financial and human resources to address society’s most pressing needs. Prudential’s Inclusive Solutions team leads the company's efforts for making positive social change core to Prudential’s business. Part of this approach includes an investment group – Prudential Impact and Responsible Investing - that has over the last 44 years invested over $2.5 billion and currently manages a portfolio of approximately $1 billion of AUM. IRI makes investments in a wide range of private asset classes. Approximately half the portfolio is in real assets, with the other half invested in private equity/credit investments. Investments are made both directly in companies/assets as well as indirectly through managers. The portfolio is also split between debt and equity investments and approximately 75% of the portfolio is invested in the United States.

Your team

You will be an Investment Analyst supporting both the real assets and the private credit/equity teams, with assignments covering both asset types and range of business sectors in line with our principal impact strategies: financial inclusion, education and reskilling, affordable housing, and transformative development. You will work directly with senior team leaders and deal team leads as well as operations support groups internal to IRI and elsewhere within Prudential.

Your role
Analyze and underwrite investment decisions on behalf of the IRI team, blending both financial and impact analysis of opportunities;
Responsibilities will consist of, but are not limited to: support of acquisitions, dispositions, development, debt financing, and ongoing portfolio management, preparing cash flow models, sensitivity tables, property valuations, and joint venture structuring;
Prepare Investment Committee memoranda and related materials through financial analysis, market research, risk analysis, and in-depth understanding of investment factors;
Support the transaction team during due diligence and closing processes.
Participate in the asset management, property budget, and strategic plan processes for a portfolio of investments;
Analyze economic, legal, political and market conditions within assigned areas;
Work closely with internal and external stakeholders: brokers, asset managers, portfolio analysts, and operations/accounting/legal teams from various partners and business relationships;
Occasional travel to support transactions and attend conferences, etc.
Your Expertise

What we are looking for in your background

What You’ll Need To Succeed
1-3 years relevant work experience;
Strong organizational skills and attention to detail with ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously;
Strong quantitative skills and demonstrated analytical ability;
Strong interpersonal/communication and business writing skills;
Understanding of basic financial statements and accounting;
Financial modeling skills including investment analysis, valuation, and sensitivity analysis
Understanding of basic financial concepts such as NOI returns, cash flow returns, internal rate of return, present value and discounted cash flow;
Understanding of equity and credit investment structures and vehicles preferred
Computer proficiency with a strong working knowledge of Microsoft Excel and Word.

It’d Be a Plus If You Have
Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Economics or Real Estate;
Understanding of basic real estate terms and concepts such as revenues, leases, rents, contracts, operating expenses, capital expenditures, and various property types;
Experience underwriting or evaluating real estate investment opportunities.
