Oliver James seleziona un Investment Analyst con esperienza nel ruolo per il team Transaction di un'importante società di investimenti immobiliari. Il nostro cliente è uno dei più prestigiosi player del mercato Real Estate e ha sede a Milano.

La risorsa inserità sarà coinvolta in tutta la fase del processo acquisitivo: dall'attività di scouting, alle relazioni con gli advisor fino all'attività di closing dell'investimento. Avrà, inoltre, la possibilità di avere una visione a 360 gradi del mercato Real Estate, lavorando su più asset e stabilendo relazioni con le principali realtà del settore - nazionali e internazionali.

Siamo alla ricerca di un profilo fortemente quantitativo in possesso delle seguenti caratteristiche:

esperienza di almeno 2-3 anni nel mondo degli investimenti: saranno valutate candidature di profili provenienti sia dal mondo Real Estate che da altri asset class;
attitudine all'analisi numerica e interesse verso la finanza quantitativa;
laurea in ambito economico-finanziario o ingegneristico;
padonanza della suite Office;
inglese fluente;
forte interesse per il mondo finance;
A fare la differenza saranno le capacità di relazionarsi in modo positivo all'interno di un team e la passione per il mondo investimenti. La nostra realtà offre interessanti opportunità di crescita sia in termini di visibilità internazionale che di sviluppo trasversale di competenze.

Offriamo un contratto a tempo indeterminato e una RAL in linea con l'esperienza del candidato.

L'appartenenza alle categorie protette (art.18) costituirà un requisito preferenziale.

SUMMARY OF POSITION:

The Investment Analyst will support the investment team in all aspects of real estate market analysis, asset underwriting, and transaction due diligence. The individual will be responsible for analytical support for the Investments Group, including preparation of financial analyses and presentations, and conducting research related to hotel acquisitions and dispositions. 

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:

Perform market research and analysis for properties and markets considered for acquisition, development or disposition;
Analyze and summarize various contracts/agreements including Ground Leases, Management Contracts, Franchise Agreements and Loan Agreements;
Perform detailed financial analysis and economic modeling including structuring cash flow models and calculation of cash-on-cash yields, IRR analysis and discounted cash flow valuations to assess viability and profitability of potential acquisitions, developments, or dispositions;
Coordinate with Feasibility, Asset Management, Corporate Finance, Tax, Accounting, Design and Construction, and other internal departments to obtain data relevant to analysis and modeling functions;
Prepare Investment recommendations including written description, quantitative and qualitative analyses, and presentations for Senior Management and the Board of Directors;
Perform and coordinate acquisition due diligence activities including but not limited to: financial analysis, title and zoning review, building evaluation coordination and review, environmental review, lease review and abstraction, and document review;
Participate in projects and assignments related to various departments of the Company, including, but not limited to ROI Analyses, Management Contract negotiations, and Leasing;
Perform other responsibilities as assigned.

EDUCATION/EXPERIENCE:

Four-year degree (or equivalent work experience) is a requirement with degree preference in finance and/or real estate; emphasis placed on the strong financial acumen, leadership and problem-solving skills;
Position requires thorough knowledge of the lodging industry and markets, hospitality operations and accounting, and real estate finance and return on investment principles. One to three years of relevant experience in the hotel finance, financial modeling and quantitative analysis, and/or commercial/hotel real estate industries is preferred;
Asset management or investments experience is a plus but not required.

REQUIRED SKILLS:

Experience in self-directed management of projects and/or processes;
Critical thinking and problem-solving skills;
Advanced MS Excel modeling skills;
Demonstrated evidence of strong financial and analytical acumen;
Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written;
Sensitivity to and respect for the confidential nature of the subject matter of the job and the department; 
Excellent interpersonal skills and a professional manner;
Team player attitude and ability to manage and train others;
High energy, enthusiasm, integrity and strong work ethic.
